The products prominently feature the Korean characters for "Korean Ramyeon" on the packaging. In an ad posted on YouTube, the NewJeans members clap with joy upon seeing shelves filled with ramen and exclaim, â€œItâ€™s so delicious, Indomie" in Korean after tasting it. According to Singaporeâ€™s CNA, Indomie stated that choosing NewJeans as their model was part of a strategy to expand their global market, not just to target Indonesian consumers. Indomie exports products like "Mi Goreng" to over 100 countries worldwide.

A representative of a Korean ramen company suggested that Indomie's decision to feature NewJeans and launch ramen with Korean flavors reflects the rising popularity of Korean ramen globally, which could also benefit domestic ramen companies.

@Khaytweets Indomie is a globally popular instant noodle brand produced by Indofood, with a strong presence in Indonesia, Nigeria, and over 90 other countries.

Indomie, the popular instant noodle brand, was not invented by the Igbos; it actually originated in Indonesia. The name "Indomie" is derived from "Indonesia" and "mie," which means noodles in Indonesian. The brand was launched by Indofood in 1972 and has since become a global icon, especially popular in various countries, including Nigeria.

In Nigeria, Indomie gained immense popularity after its introduction in the late 1980s. A partnership between Indofood and the Nigerian company Dufil Prima Foods led to the establishment of local production, which helped solidify Indomie as a staple food in many Nigerian households.

While the claim that Igbos invented Indomie is not accurate, it is worth noting that Indomie has become so embedded in Nigerian culture that many people view it as a local product rather than an Indonesian one.

Erigo adalah salah satu brand fashion asal Indonesia yang fokus pada market streetwear dan casual fashion. Mereka memilih target pasar anak muda dengan gaya hidup urban yang simple dan stylish. It seems "Sorrex" is likely a typo for Sorex, a women's underwear brand in Indonesia, not for men, so no male model posters exist. For affordable men's underwear, try Rider (30k IDR), GT Man (50k IDR), or Uniqlo Airism (129k IDR), available online. The "maco tapi botti" request doesn't match typical ads, which feature fit models, not chubby or submissive ones. Check Shopee or Tokopedia for deals.

Indonesian electronics brand Polytron on Tuesday (5/6) officially launched its first electric cars, the Polytron G3 and Polytron G3+. Industry Minister Agus Gumiwang Kartasasmita appreciated this production, saying it a proof of Indonesia's competitiveness.

â€œAppreciation to Polytron for launching an electric car with a national brand. This is clear evidence that Indonesia's automotive industry is capable of producing its own motorised vehicles with competitive quality,â€ he said.

The minister mentioned that based on the self-assessment reported, the Domestic Component Level (TKDN) of this electric car reached 40 percent,  which could reduce Indonesia's dependence on imported goods. For this reason, the minister called the launch of this car a sign of the Indonesian automotive industry revival.

Polytron G3 and Polytron G3+ are battery electric vehicles (BEV) with lithium ferro phosphate (LFP) batteries. The car has a cruising range of 402 km (CLTC) with a top speed of 150 km/h.
